com.eclipsesource.v8

Class V8Array

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Value
      • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Object
        • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Array
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Releasable

    public class V8Array
extends V8Object
    A V8Value that represents a JavaScript array. JavaScript Arrays contain elements by index, but can also contain elements by 'key' which is why V8Array extends V8Object.

      • twin

        public V8Array twin()
        Description copied from class: V8Value
        Creates a new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this. If the value is mutated (by adding new members or changing existing ones) then both the original and twin will be updated. Twins are .equal and .strict equals, but not == in Java. Twins must be released separately since they have their own native resources.
        Overrides:
        twin in class V8Object
        Returns:
        A new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this.

      • getIntegers

        public int getIntegers(int index,
              int length,
              int[] resultArray)
        Gets the integers contained in a subset of a V8Array. If the subset contains elements other than integers, then a V8ResultUndefined exception is thrown. Furthermore, if the subset is not entirely contained within the array, then V8ResultUndefined exception is also thrown. Finally, if the resultArray is not large enough to hold the results then IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown.

        length - The length.
